Halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks.

Trim and thinly slice the @Spring Onion{1}. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Remove the @Pineapple Rings{1} from the tin (keep the juice for the sauce) and cut into 2cm chunks.

Pour the cold @Water for the Rice{300%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, pour the pineapple juice into a #bowl{} and add the @Rice Vinegar{30%ml}, garlic and @Soy Sauce{15%ml}.

Stir in the @Tomato Ketchup{3%tbsp}, @Sugar for the Sauce{1.5%tbsp} and @Water for the Sauce{75%ml}.

Mix together until fully combined, then set your sauce aside.

Pop the @Diced Chicken Breast{260%g} into a bowl with the @Cornflour{10%g}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the chicken and fry until golden brown and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. Discard any cornflour left in the bowl.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the chicken has browned, transfer it to a clean bowl and set aside.

Lower the heat to medium-high and add the pepper to the (now empty) frying pan. Stir-fry until just soft and charred, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the pineapple and stir-fry for a further ~{1-2%minutes}, then add the cooked chicken and sauce.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and gently simmer until slightly thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Taste the chicken and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if needed, adding a splash of @water{} if it's a little thick.

When ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the sweet and sour chicken, then sprinkle over the spring onion to finish. Enjoy!